    <briefdescription>
<para>Deferred triviality evaluator for Vector&lt;T&gt;. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Vector&lt;T&gt; uses this as its default second template argument instead of reading <ref refid="structDali_1_1BasicTypes_1a6f0ae269d7db2eb396e42bea75cf2919a6341d72bffa3d4b094b164d9d1367573" kindref="member">TypeTraits&lt;T&gt;::IS_TRIVIAL_TYPE</ref> directly. This is necessary because default template arguments for class templates are evaluated whenever the template name is used — including in type aliases and forward declarations — which would fire the compiler intrinsics in BasicTypes&lt;T&gt; before T is complete.</para>
<para>By placing the intrinsics inside this helper struct, they are only evaluated when VectorIsTrivial&lt;T&gt; is explicitly instantiated, which only happens when Vector&lt;T&gt; itself is instantiated (i.e. when T is complete).</para>
<para>The unused Dummy parameter prevents aggressive compilers (MSVC, GCC with -fno-implicit-templates) from pre-instantiating the value member when they see the ::value reference in the default argument.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The element type of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Vector" kindref="compound">Vector</ref> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Dummy</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Unused; keeps the body dependent so it is not pre-instantiated </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
